Test Case Specification
Format: Each test case follows this structure:

TC-ID: Unique identifier
Test Objective: What we're validating
Preconditions: Setup requirements
Test Steps: Detailed actions
Expected Result: Success criteria
Test Data: Input values
Priority: High/Medium/Low
Test Type: Functional/Negative/API

SAMPLE TEST CASE (Detailed)

TC-001: Verify Popular Category Filter
Objective: Validate that clicking "Popular" category displays popular movies/shows
Priority: High
Type: Functional
Preconditions: Application is accessible

Test Steps:
Navigate to https://tmdb-discover.surge.sh/
Verify default category is loaded
Click on "Popular" category button
Wait for content to load
Verify URL updates appropriately
Capture network request to TMDB API
Validate response contains "popular" endpoint

Expected Result:
Popular category is highlighted
Grid displays popular titles
Network request to /movie/popular or /tv/popular successful
Response status: 200
At least 1 result displayed
Test Data: N/A

==============================================================================================================

TC-035: Verify Combined Filters - Category + Type + Year
Objective: Test multiple simultaneous filters

Priority: High
Type: Integration

Test Steps:
Select Category: "Top Rated"
Select Type: "Movies"
Apply Year filter: 2020
Apply Rating filter: â‰¥ 8
Verify all filters remain active
Validate API request contains all filter parameters
Verify results match ALL criteria

Expected Result:

All filter selections persist
Single API request with combined parameters
Results satisfy all filter conditions
Filter badges/indicators show active filters
Test Data:
Category: Top Rated
Type: Movies
Year: 2020
Rating: 8+

